Método 1: GPO com QoS Policy (Recomendado)
Criando a GPO
1. Abrir Group Policy Management Console:

Criar nova GPO: "Limitacao_Velocidade_SMB"
Aplicar na OU desejada

2. Navegar para:
Computer Configuration > Policies > Windows Settings > Policy-based QoS
3. Criar Política QoS:

Clique direito > "Create new policy"
Policy name: "Limitar_SMB_2Mbps"
Specify DSCP Value: 8 (CS1 - Baixa prioridade)
Specify Outbound Throttle Rate: 2048 Kbps (2 Mbps)

4. Configurar Application:

Selecionar: "All applications"

5. Configurar Source and Destination IPs:

Source IP: Any IP address
Destination IP: This IP address or subnet: IP_DO_SERVIDOR/24 (ex: 192.168.1.10/24)

6. Configurar Protocol and Ports:

Protocol: TCP
From this source port: Any
To this destination port: 445 (SMB)

#####################
TESTAR COM POWERSHELL

# Verificar políticas QoS
Get-NetQosPolicy | Where-Object {$_.Name -like "*SMB*"}

# Verificar configuração
Get-NetQosFlowControl

# Testar velocidade
Test-NetConnection -ComputerName "servidor" -Port 445 -InformationLevel Detailed
